The paper discusses the security and reliability of biometric systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a new framework for implementing biometric systems based on physical unclonable functions (PUFs) and hardware obfuscation, which involves hardware design and optimization (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of various biometric modalities, including fingerprint, iris, ECG, and PPG, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the usability and convenience of biometric systems, which falls under human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
